": "Medium"}, {"time_utc": "21:00", "currency": "USD", "title": "President Trump Speaks", "impact": "Medium"}], "editorial": "Cable is trading at 1.3505 as Thursday's session gets under way, consolidating just beneath the prior session's multi-week high of 1.3558 after yesterday's sharp impulsive advance. The daily chart tells a compelling recovery story: from the mid-June lows near 1.3142, the pair has constructed a sequence of higher lows and, with Tuesday's breakout candle printing the largest bullish range in the recent window, the structure has shifted decisively in sterling's favour. The desk's bias sits firmly bullish.\n\nThe structure story begins with the prolonged base that formed between late June and early July, where price compressed into a tight range around 1.3190\u20131.3260 for the better part of three weeks. That accumulation resolved cleanly to the upside on 2 July, and the subsequent grind higher through the 1.33\u20131.34 handle has been orderly, with each daily close respecting the developing trend. The prior reaction zone at 1.3483 \u2014 a level that attracted five separate touches on the way up \u2014 now functions as the first meaningful structural support beneath current price. Below that, the 1.3452 zone offers a secondary layer of prior reaction interest. To the upside, the structure resistance at 1.3512 is the immediate overhead reference; it has capped two prior approaches and sits only a handful of pips above the current print, making it the key near-term battleground.\n\nOn the H1 chart, the picture is one of healthy consolidation following the impulsive leg that carried price from 1.3429 to the 1.3558 session high during the early hours of Wednesday. Since that peak, the hourly sequence has been a controlled drift lower, with each candle printing relatively modest ranges and the pair finding a floor in the 1.3495\u20131.3506 area through the late New York and Asian hours. There is no sign of aggressive distribution; the pullback reads as digestion rather than reversal, and the pair remains well above the 1.3483 prior reaction zone on an hourly closing basis.\n\nThe calendar is loaded today. UK GDP month-on-month at 02:00 UTC has already passed through the window, and any surprise in that print will have coloured early positioning. The more significant cluster arrives at 08:30 UTC, with US Retail Sales, Core Retail Sales, Philly Fed Manufacturing, and Weekly Unemployment Claims all landing simultaneously \u2014 a combination that can generate sharp, whipsaw-style moves in dollar pairs. A materially softer US consumption print would likely provide fresh tailwinds for the bullish scenario, whilst a beat could see the dollar reassert itself and test the 1.3483 support zone in earnest. Later, President Trump speaking at 21:00 UTC carries headline risk that could extend volatility into the close.\n\nThe bullish read would come under pressure on a sustained hourly close beneath the 1.3483 prior reaction zone, and would be materially challenged by any daily close back beneath 1.3452. A clean break and hold above the 1.3512 structure resistance, by contrast, would open the path toward the 1.3558 recent high and beyond.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}